      "content": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph \"><span class=\"align align-16\">72</span></p>\n"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [
    "d"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. There are 60 minutes in one hour, so an 8-hour workday has <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"60 times 8, equals 480\"></span> minutes. To calculate 15% of 480, multiply 0.15 by 480: <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"0 point 1 5 times 480, equals 72\"></span>. Therefore, Lani spent 72 minutes of her workday in meetings.<p>Choice A is incorrect because 1.2 is 15% of 8, which gives the time Lani spent of her workday in meetings in hours, not minutes. Choices B and C are incorrect and may be the result of computation errors.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
